Paracetamol,ABC Pharmaceuticals,Paracetamol 500mg tablets,Box of 30 tablets,5,Store in a cool, dry place,Paracetamol is a common pain reliever,Paracetamol is used to treat mild to moderate pain,Headache, fever, muscle aches, toothache, backache, arthritis, and cold/flu symptoms,Take 1 tablet every 4-6 hours as needed for pain,Paracetamol reduces fever and relieves pain by inhibiting the production of certain chemicals in the brain that cause pain and fever.,Do not exceed the recommended dosage. Consult your doctor if symptoms persist.,If you miss a dose, take it as soon as you remember. If it is near the time of your next dose, skip the missed dose and resume your usual dosing schedule.,Drink plenty of fluids and get rest to help your body recover from illness.,Tell your doctor about all the medicines you take, including prescription and non-prescription medicines, herbal supplements, and vitamins.,Paracetamol may cause liver damage if taken in high doses or for a long time.,Paracetamol may interact with other drugs, so inform your doctor if you are taking any other medications.,Some patients may experience nausea, vomiting, or allergic reactions to Paracetamol.,4.5,USD
Ibuprofen,XYZ Pharma,Ibuprofen 200mg capsules,Box of 50 capsules,8,Store at room temperature away from moisture and heat,Ibuprofen is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID),Ibuprofen is used to relieve pain from various conditions such as headache, dental pain, menstrual cramps, muscle aches, or arthritis. It is also used to reduce fever and to relieve minor aches and pain due to the common cold or flu.,Stomach pain, heartburn, nausea, vomiting, headache, dizziness, or diarrhea may occur. If any of these effects persist or worsen, tell your doctor or pharmacist promptly.,Take 1 capsule by mouth every 4 to 6 hours as needed for pain relief.,Ibuprofen works by blocking the production of certain natural substances that cause inflammation and pain in the body.,Avoid alcohol and smoking while taking Ibuprofen. Consult your doctor if you have any concerns about drug interactions or side effects.,If you miss a dose, take it as soon as you remember. If it is near the time of your next dose, skip the missed dose. Do not double the dose to catch up.,Rest and apply cold packs or compression to the affected area to reduce inflammation and pain.,Tell your doctor about all other medicines you use, especially: aspirin, diuretics, lithium, methotrexate, corticosteroids, or ACE inhibitors.,Ibuprofen may increase your risk of heart attack or stroke. Do not use this medicine just before or after heart bypass surgery (coronary artery bypass graft, or CABG).,Ibuprofen may interact with other drugs, so inform your doctor if you are taking any other medications.,Some patients may experience stomach upset, heartburn, or dizziness while taking Ibuprofen.,4.2,USD
Amoxicillin,PharmaTech,Amoxicillin 250mg/5ml oral suspension,Bottle of 100ml suspension,10,Store in a refrigerator, away from heat and moisture,Amoxicillin is an antibiotic used to treat a wide variety of bacterial infections.,Amoxicillin is used to treat infections caused by bacteria, such as ear infections, bladder infections, pneumonia, gonorrhea, and E. coli or salmonella infection.,Nausea, vomiting, or diarrhea may occur. If any of these effects persist or worsen, tell your doctor or pharmacist promptly.,Shake the suspension well before each use. Take this medication by mouth with or without food as directed by your doctor, usually every 8 or 12 hours.,Amoxicillin works by stopping the growth of bacteria.,Take Amoxicillin exactly as prescribed by your doctor. Do not take more or less of it or take it more often than prescribed by your doctor.,If you miss a dose, take it as soon as you remember. However, if it is almost time for the next dose, skip the missed dose and continue your regular dosing schedule. Do not take a double dose to make up for a missed one.,Drink plenty of fluids while taking Amoxicillin to help reduce the risk of side effects.,Before using this medication, tell your doctor or pharmacist your medical history, especially of: kidney disease, a certain type of viral infection (infectious mononucleosis).,Amoxicillin may cause false positive results with certain diabetic urine testing products (cupric sulfate-type).,Amoxicillin may interact with other drugs, so inform your doctor if you are taking any other medications.,Some patients may experience mild diarrhea or stomach upset while taking Amoxicillin.,4.8,USD
Loratadine,HealthCare Inc.,Loratadine 10mg tablets,Box of 30 tablets,6,Store at room temperature away from light and moisture,Loratadine is an antihistamine used to relieve symptoms of allergies, such as runny nose, sneezing, itching, and watery eyes.,Loratadine is used to treat symptoms such as itching, runny nose, and sneezing from "hay fever" and other allergies.,Drowsiness, headache, fatigue, dry mouth, nosebleed, sore throat, or muscle pain may occur. If any of these effects persist or worsen, tell your doctor or pharmacist promptly.,Take 1 tablet by mouth once daily with or without food.,Loratadine works by blocking the action of histamine, a substance in the body that causes allergic symptoms.,Avoid using Loratadine with alcohol or other medications that may cause drowsiness.,If you miss a dose, take it as soon as you remember. If it is near the time of the next dose, skip the missed dose and resume your usual dosing schedule. Do not double the dose to catch up.,Drink plenty of fluids to stay hydrated and reduce dry mouth while taking Loratadine.,Before using this medication, tell your doctor or pharmacist your medical history, especially of: kidney disease.,Loratadine may cause drowsiness, so avoid driving or operating machinery until you know how this medicine affects you.,Loratadine may interact with other drugs, so inform your doctor if you are taking any other medications.,Some patients may experience drowsiness or dry mouth while taking Loratadine.,4.6,USD
Omeprazole,MediCure Pharmaceuticals,Omeprazole 20mg capsules,Box of 28 capsules,12,Store at room temperature away from moisture and heat,Omeprazole is a proton pump inhibitor used to treat conditions caused by excess stomach acid.,Omeprazole is used to treat symptoms of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD) and other conditions caused by excess stomach acid.,Headache, diarrhea, stomach pain, nausea, or vomiting may occur. If any of these effects persist or worsen, tell your doctor or pharmacist promptly.,Take 1 capsule by mouth once daily before a meal, usually in the morning.,Omeprazole works by reducing the amount of acid your stomach produces.,Take Omeprazole exactly as prescribed by your doctor. Do not take more or less of it or take it more often than prescribed by your doctor.,If you miss a dose, take it as soon as you remember. If it is almost time for the next dose, skip the missed dose and continue your regular dosing schedule. Do not take a double dose to make up for a missed one.,Eat smaller meals and avoid spicy or acidic foods to help reduce stomach discomfort while taking Omeprazole.,Before using this medication, tell your doctor or pharmacist your medical history, especially of: liver disease.,Omeprazole may increase your risk of bone fracture, especially with long-term use or high doses. Talk to your doctor about ways to prevent bone loss.,Omeprazole may interact with other drugs, so inform your doctor if you are taking any other medications.,Some patients may experience headache, diarrhea, or stomach pain while taking Omeprazole.,4.3,USD
